---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="LSCSS Learning Paths"
    description="Recommended learning and implementation paths for Layered Semantic CSS."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Learning paths</p>

        <h1>
            Learning and implementation paths
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            The previous tools collection is currently being reassessed.
            Use these documentation paths for practical implementation guidance.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Start here
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/learn/what-is-lscss/">What is LSCSS?</a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Get the quick overview before choosing migration or implementation routes.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/learn/principles/">Principles</a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Learn the non-negotiables that keep CSS maintainable over time.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    <a href="/apply/decision-trees/">Decision trees</a>
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Use practical rules for ownership, state, utilities, and override decisions.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Architecture and debugging guidance
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/apply/layers/">Layers</a></h3>
                <p>Control precedence with architecture before increasing selector complexity.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/apply/architecture/">Architecture</a></h3>
                <p>Use predictable file ownership and component structure for safer changes.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/apply/migration/">Migration</a></h3>
                <p>Improve legacy CSS incrementally without stopping delivery.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>Quality and compatibility</h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/writing/guides/accessibility-and-css/">Accessibility and CSS</a></h3>
                <p>Apply accessibility patterns across state, theme, and component layers.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/writing/guides/browser-support-strategy/">Browser support strategy</a></h3>
                <p>Define support policy based on feature needs and progressive enhancement.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>Performance and rendering</h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/writing/guides/performance-and-css/">Performance and CSS</a></h3>
                <p>Prioritize architecture choices that reduce long-term rendering and maintenance cost.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3><a href="/apply/theme-layer/">Theme layer</a></h3>
                <p>Keep visual changes predictable so theme overrides do not create hidden performance issues.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

</DocsLayout>
